### FINDINGS
[F-008-01] ADAPT: Replace the single self-attested checklist checkbox with an AC traceability table: `AC-id | classification (Tested/Partially/Manual/Not-covered) | evidence (test name @ file:line)`. Peck already maps each AC to `Tested / Partially tested / Manual / Not covered` and cites `"test name" (file:line)`; spec-kit currently collapses this to `CHK-020 [P0] All acceptance criteria met`. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:36-42`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:69-76`. GAP: no per-AC evidence table. EFFORT: S. RISK: low, template-only until validator consumes it. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl` testing section; optional summary row update.

[F-008-02] ADAPT: Add `AC_COVERAGE` validation with `covered = Tested + Partially + Manual`, `covered/total >= floor(total * SPECKIT_AC_COVERAGE_FLOOR)`, default floor `0.9`. Peck uses `covered ≥ floor(0.9 × task_ACs)` and blocks overall pass on every task; spec-kit’s validation model already supports `WARNING` vs strict-mode blocking, but `EVIDENCE_CITED` only checks generic evidence tokens. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:42`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:27-35`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:424-453`. GAP: no computed AC coverage ratio. EFFORT: M. RISK: medium from false blocks on old/in-flight folders. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md`; validator registry/rule implementation; `CLAUDE.md` §2 completion verification lines 247-252.

[F-008-03] ADAPT: Stage `AC_COVERAGE` rollout as `WARNING` first, then `ERROR` after template adoption; strict validation already turns warnings into exit-2 validation failures, so the first stage can still protect completion without instantly breaking non-strict workflows. peck’s acceptance reviewer is binary Pass/Fail and blocking; spec-kit’s severity table gives the migration lever. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:79-83`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:29-35`. GAP: existing evidence rule is warning-only and not AC-semantic. EFFORT: S. RISK: low-medium. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md`; `CLAUDE.md` §2 completion verification lines 247-252.

[F-008-04] ADAPT: Preserve Peck’s manual escape hatch, but make it explicit: `Manual - automation infeasible` counts as covered only with evidence and rationale. Peck allows `Manual` only when automation is infeasible; spec-kit has a generic manual testing checkbox but no per-AC manual classification. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:39-42`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl:72-75`. GAP: manual evidence is checklist-level, not AC-level. EFFORT: S. RISK: gaming risk if rationale is not reviewed. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md`.

[F-008-05] ADAPT: Bind final AC coverage verdict to fresh-context `deep-review`, not the implementer. Peck’s implementer cannot mark done until a separate acceptance reviewer and code reviewer both pass; spec-kit now has a fresh-context review loop with PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL verdicts and spec-alignment/traceability as a review dimension. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/README.md:28-33`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:310-327`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:341-367`. GAP: completion verification is still implementer-driven checklist marking. EFFORT: M. RISK: medium due workflow coupling. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md`; `CLAUDE.md` §2 completion verification lines 247-252.

[F-008-06] ADAPT: Make `AC_COVERAGE` opt-in by documentation level: default enabled for Level 2+ once `checklist.md` exists; Level 1 remains exempt unless a folder explicitly opts in. Peck assumes every task AC is automatable; spec-kit Level 1 does not require `checklist.md`, and `CLAUDE.md` explicitly skips Level 1 checklist completion. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/story.md:21-27`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:70-75`, `CLAUDE.md:247-252`. GAP: spec-kit levels intentionally vary verification weight. EFFORT: S. RISK: low. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl`; `CLAUDE.md` §2.

[F-008-07] ADOPT-AS-PACKET: T1 should be its own packet, not a sub-phase of the proposed 006 sub-packet. The original deferral rationale was “largest blast radius” and “separate future packet”; the current design still touches the checklist template, validation rule docs/registry, completion verification, and deep-review verdict binding, so it is now adoptable but still packet-sized. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/README.md:30-35`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/spec.md:64-84`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/spec.md:131-133`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/001-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/peck-teachings-analysis.md:297-301`. GAP: no current packet owns the completion-gate blast radius. EFFORT: M/L. RISK: medium. BLAST-RADIUS: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md`; `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md`; `CLAUDE.md` §2.

### RULED_OUT
- Do not rebuild AC syntax from scratch: spec-kit already has L1/L2 `Acceptance Criteria` columns and L3/L3+ Given/When/Then user-story ACs. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:89-97`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:526-543`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl:765-772`.
- Do not rebuild evidence infrastructure: `EVIDENCE_CITED` already recognizes `[Test: ...]`, `[File: ...]`, `[Commit: ...]`, and reviewer evidence patterns. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:424-445`.
- Do not create a new reviewer primitive: `deep-review` already has fresh context, spec-alignment/traceability, and parseable PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL verdicts. `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:310-327`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:341-367`.

